  "prompt": "What is nag mani?",
  "response": "Nag Mani, also known as Serpent's Jewel or Snake Stone, is a legendary gemstone often mentioned in Hindu mythology and folklore. It is believed to be a precious stone found inside the hood of a king cobra or other serpents. The stone is said to possess mystical and supernatural powers, including the ability to bring wealth, good fortune, and protection from evil.\n\nIn various tales, Nag Mani is described as glowing with an inner light and is often associated with the Naga, a race of serpent deities in Hindu and Buddhist mythology. The stone is considered extremely rare and valuable, and possessing one is believed to confer great spiritual and material benefits.\n\nHowever, there is no scientific evidence to support the existence of Nag Mani, and it remains a part of cultural and religious lore.",
